3#ifndef __NVKM_I2C_PRIV_H__
4#define __NVKM_I2C_PRIV_H__
5#define nvkm_i2c(p) container_of((p), struct nvkm_i2c, subdev)
6#include <subdev/i2c.h>
7
8int nvkm_i2c_new_(const struct nvkm_i2c_func *, struct nvkm_device *,
9 int index, struct nvkm_i2c **);
10
11struct nvkm_i2c_func {
12 int (*pad_x_new)(struct nvkm_i2c *, int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad **);
13 int (*pad_s_new)(struct nvkm_i2c *, int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad **);
14
15 /* number of native dp aux channels present */
16 int aux;
17
18 /* read and ack pending interrupts, returning only data
19 * for ports that have not been masked off, while still
20 * performing the ack for anything that was pending.
21 */
22 void (*aux_stat)(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *);
23
24 /* mask on/off interrupt types for a given set of auxch
25 */
26 void (*aux_mask)(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32, u32, u32);
27};
28
29void g94_aux_stat(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *);
30void g94_aux_mask(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32, u32, u32);
31
32void gk104_aux_stat(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *, u32 *);
33void gk104_aux_mask(struct nvkm_i2c *, u32, u32, u32);
34#endif
